QUEEN ROCKET set the pace along the rail, steadied entering the first turn, led to midstretch, was forced in by BOMBA NERA leaving the eighth pole, bumped KING'S SECRET and lost the whip in the incident then dropped back. READY SHE IS was bumped between foes not long after the start, steadied a few strides later, tracked the pace three wide, was forced out in upper stretch and weakened. JUST THE SKY saved ground and failed to menace. KING'S SECRET (GB) saved ground off the pace, bid at the rail nearing the eighth pole, was bumped and forced to take up leaving the eighth pole and was not urged from there. APRIATI was off slow, saved ground off the pace, went five wide around the far turn and never threatened. KEKIONGA played no factor while racing two and three wide. TAR HEEL GIRL was bumped between foes not long after the start, raced up close two wide, steadied near the five-eighths pole and steadily faded. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE INCIDENT IN THE STRETCH AND DISQUALIFIED BOMBA NERA FROM FOURTH AND PLACED HER EIGHTH FOR CAUSING INTERFERENCE LEAVING THE EIGHTH POLE.
